will a beta be mean to a molly i have a dalmation molly and i might get another fish i have always heard of beta's being mean to other fish and sometimes mollies bieng mean to other fish i have also read that the mollies are good to eachother and same with beta so which are they mean or not male bettas are only aggressive towards other males and sometimes female bettas if they are kept in close quarters and she doesn't reciprocate his advances male and female bettas are not however aggressive towards other fish if anything other fish have a tendency to nip at the long flowing tails of male bettas i haven't really had any problems with my mollies i have black and sunset mollies with neon black neons blue tetras banded topminnows pearl gourami etc attacking or being aggressive with any of my other fish the most aggressive fish that i've personally dealt with in a tropical tank environment fin nippers etc have been flying foxes chinese butterflies and barbs Betta (Siamese Fighting Fish) Dwarf gourami Gourami Danio Sailfin Molly Nickname Neon tetra USS Tunny (SS-282) Kissing gourami Discus (fish) USS Flying Fish (SS-229) The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll Minor Harry Potter Beasts Flyingfish Cardinal tetra Stingray D'ni wildlife Clownfish Seabird Perciformes Schuylkill County, Pennsylvania Whale Gar Mindless Self Indulgence USS Thresher (SS-200) Cat Johnny Depp Sexual selection Marine aquarium Fishing Sonic the Hedgehog 2 Glossary of nautical terms Dr. Seuss Liam Gallagher USS Ray (SS-271) Attack on Pearl Harbor Characiformes Gray Wolf Batoidea Parrotfish Heavy metal music Bedknobs and Broomsticks White Cloud Mountain Minnow Neuromancer USS Wahoo (SS-238) Humpback Whale Fauna of Australia Poker jargon USS Intrepid (CV-11) Platypus W.A.S.P. Isle of Wight Sport Koi Spider The Legend of Zelda: The Wind Waker characters Tilapia F-104 Starfighter USS Tinosa (SS-283) Pearl Jam Halfbeak Bottlenose Dolphin Shark Nip/Tuck Chinatown Fin Whale Cha